    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> on top, dot them with a few knobs of <strong>butter alternative</strong> and sprinkle with<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped thyme</strong></p><p>Put the dish on a baking tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are brown and crispy – this is your<strong> Lancashire-style lentil hotpot</strong></p><p>Once the Lancashire-style lentil hotpot is done, remove it from the oven and set aside to cool a little (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p>",
